//@version=6

// =============================================================================
// Webhook EMA Cross (template)
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Minimal Pine strategy that fires webhook alerts compatible with this repo's
// generic signal endpoint. See docs/webhooks.md for the full JSON schema and
// portfolio-sizing/execution behaviour on the receiving end.
//
// Swap `longCondition` / `exitCondition` for your own entry/exit logic — the
// `alert()` wiring at the bottom is the reusable part; everything above it is
// just an example signal (fast/slow EMA cross) so the script runs as-is.
//
// One-time setup in TradingView:
//   1. Add this script to a chart (Pine Editor → paste → "Add to chart").
//      `strategy()` (rather than `indicator()`) also gives you the Strategy
//      Tester tab for a quick backtest of the example logic, but is not
//      required for the webhook itself — the alert() calls fire independently
//      of strategy.entry/close.
//   2. Right-click the chart → Add alert (or the bell icon). Condition =
//      this script, "Any alert() function call". Trigger = "Once Per Bar
//      Close" (belt-and-braces with alert.freq_once_per_bar_close below —
//      avoids duplicate/intrabar-repaint fires).
//   3. Under Notifications, enable "Webhook URL" and paste:
//        https://<your-domain>/api/webhooks/signal?token=<WEBHOOK_TOKEN>
//      (Webhook alerts require a paid TradingView plan — Essential or above.)
//   4. Leave the alert's Message box untouched — each alert() call below
//      supplies its own JSON body, the dialog's message field is unused.
// =============================================================================

strategy(
     "Webhook EMA Cross (template)",
     overlay             = true,
     default_qty_type    = strategy.percent_of_equity,
     default_qty_value   = 100,
     calc_on_every_tick  = false)

fastLen = input.int(20, "Fast EMA length")
slowLen = input.int(50, "Slow EMA length")
botName = input.string("pine-ema-cross", "bot_name sent in webhook payload")

fastMA = ta.ema(close, fastLen)
slowMA = ta.ema(close, slowLen)

longCondition = ta.crossover(fastMA, slowMA)
exitCondition = ta.crossunder(fastMA, slowMA)

if longCondition
    strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long)

if exitCondition
    strategy.close("Long")

plot(fastMA, "Fast EMA", color = color.new(color.teal, 0))
plot(slowMA, "Slow EMA", color = color.new(color.orange, 0))

// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Webhook payload — field names match lib/webhook-schema.ts on the receiving
// app. Only `symbol` + `action` are required there; `source`/`bot_name`/
// `timeframe`/`comment` are optional metadata carried through to the
// dashboard's webhook-events log. Quantity/price are always resolved
// server-side (see docs/webhooks.md), so none is sent here.
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
buildPayload(action, comment) =>
    '{"symbol":"'   + syminfo.ticker    +
     '","action":"' + action            +
     '","source":"tradingview"'         +
     ',"bot_name":"' + botName          +
     '","timeframe":"' + timeframe.period +
     '","comment":"' + comment + '"}'

if longCondition
    alert(buildPayload("buy", "ema-cross-entry"), alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

if exitCondition
    alert(buildPayload("sell", "ema-cross-exit"), alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
